THE talent of Evening Times photographers is on show at an exhbition depicting Scottish identity. a snapshot of scotland THE talent of Evening Times photographers is on show at an exhbition depicting Scottish identity.Although the theme is 'Scottish Identity' the exhibition at The Hidden Gallery on Argyll Street includes images taken in The Bahamas, China, Brazil, as well as far flung corners of Scotland.The imagery is a mix of portraits, politics, landscapes, sport, nature, features, the arts and on the spot news stories that says something about Scotland and its identity.The brief to photographers was to keep it as open as possible - they could interpret the brief as tartan or as tenuous as they wished.And images could be new or from their archive.In total the exhibition represents 35 photographers working in the editorial photography within Scotland.The show runs until October 11, Tuesday to Saturday and from 11am to 5pm. 